1 31-7-105. Administrative hearings.
2
3 (e) The licensee has twenty (20) days from the date
4 the department denies the license or gives the notice of
5 intent to suspend, revoke or cancel the license or
6 disqualify the licensee from driving a commercial motor
7 vehicle within which to request a hearing or the
8 opportunity for a hearing is waived. If the request for a
9 hearing is timely and the request is for a contested case,
10 the department shall forward the request and certified
11 record to the hearing examiner who shall schedule a hearing
12 within forty-five (45) days after receipt of the certified
13 record at a time and place specified by the hearing
14 examiner. The hearing examiner shall provide the licensee
15 notice of the hearing at least ten (10) days in advance of
16 the hearing. If the hearing examiner fails to schedule the
17 hearing within forty-five (45) days of the request receipt
18 of the certified record from the department, other than at
19 the request of the licensee, the licensee, as his sole
20 remedy, shall be given credit against any action upheld at
21 the hearing for the time between the expiration of the
22 forty-five (45) day period and the date the hearing was
23 first scheduled. The hearing examiner may administer oaths,
