4 1994, a license and shall expire no later than when the
5 licensee attains twenty-one (21) years of age. The
6 department shall notify the licensee at least ninety (90)
7 days prior to his twenty-first birthday of the expiration
8 date of his license. A licensee may apply for a license
9 within ninety (90) days of attaining the age of twenty-one
10 (21) years, payment of the proper fee and surrender of the
11 original license in accordance with W.S. 31-7-119(a).
